Which mainstream hosters don&#x27;t? The same ones that only support and will only ever support PHP?<p>> b) having to code a server in javascript&#x27;s callback/promise hell.<p>Don&#x27;t really see promises as hell, but with latest versions of Node and this neat little library called co, you can write your async code like this:<p><pre><code>    function doAsyncOne() {} // returns promise
    function doAsyncTwo() {} // returns promise

    co(function*() {
        try {
            let [resultOne, resultTwo] = yield [doAsyncOne(), doAsyncTwo()];
        }
        catch(e) {
            // one of the promises rejected, handle it
        }
    });
</code></pre>
Generators as coroutines are the poor man&#x27;s async/await.
